        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 23 at 5:43PM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 543 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Chico, or 12 miles northwest of Bridgeport, moving northeast at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Lake Amon G Carter around 550 PM CDT.
Sunset around 555 PM CDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Fruitland, Park
Springs, Cundiff, and Crafton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
